 Midlands Correspondent A KWEKWE prophetess has been arraigned following the death of one of her patients after consuming a concoction she administered to her. Evelyn Madhara (28), of 16128 Mbizo Section 15 in Kwekwe, a self-proclaimed traditional healer, appeared before Kwekwe Magistrate Mrs Rosemary Dube facing culpable homicide charges. Beatrice Masundire died upon admission after she drank a ‘chaliced’ concoction by the faith healer. Madhara was not asked to plead and remanded in custody to September 5.